WEBVTT

00:09:28.120 --> 00:09:31.056
That's a step you can take
to build trust in your team.

00:09:31.080 --> 00:09:32.576
Whenever I work with new people

00:09:32.600 --> 00:09:35.320
I tell them that one of mine
is when someone ignores data.

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:39.056
Whatever your colleagues'
emotional triggers are,

00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:42.416
you're more likely to learn about them
when you interact under stress.

00:09:42.440 --> 00:09:45.856
JA: I think you have to get to the point

00:09:45.880 --> 00:09:47.120
where you disagree.

00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:50.696
And disagree at an emotional level.

00:09:50.720 --> 00:09:54.416
That is accelerated
by adversity in my mind,

00:09:54.440 --> 00:09:59.056
which is why we took our crews
to the canyons in winter.

00:09:59.080 --> 00:10:00.456
There was very little water,